The police have arrested two pastors and rescued 77 persons, including children locked in an underground enclosure in a church in Ondo. The Nigerian Tribune reports that Enoch Adeboye, general overseer of the RCCG, declares that it’s “fire for fire” against attacks on Christians. The newspaper says 77 persons, including children, were rescued from an underground enclosure in a church in Ondo. It also reports that the PDP accused the APC, INEC of planning to use fake BVAS for Osun governorship election. The Nation reports that the All Progressives Congress (APC) has warned senators not to defect unless they are ready to lose their seats. The newspaper says the Indepedent National Electoral Commission (INEC) is monitoring the security situation in Osun ahead of the July 16 governorship election. Daily Trust reports that there are growing concerns over President Muhammadu Buhari’s incessant foreign travels. The newspaper says Kano residents have resorted to wood, charcoal as cooking gas eludes them. The Sun reports that Ohaneze Ndi Igbo says political injustice in the south-east will end in the geopolitical zone soon. The newspaper says some leaders of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) are moving to sack Iyorchia Ayu, the national chairman. 